    <note type="biography">
        <p>Edinburgh publishing house ; from 1834, a partnership between Adam Black (1784–1874) and his nephew Charles Black (1807–54). Publishers of the <hi rend="italic">Encyclopedia Britannica</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh Review</hi>. Acquired the rights to Walter Scott’s Waverley novels in 1851.</p></note>
